  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\nWhen having a lot of validators, local antislashing DB can grow up to dozen of GB.\r\n\r\nA cool feature: Implement the minimal slashing db (with a `--mimimal-slashing-db` feature flag).\r\n[EIP-3076: Slashing Protection Interchange Format](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3076)\r\n\r\n\r\n------------\r\n## Deprecated: First ticket proposal\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen having a lot of validators, local antislashing DB can grow up to dozen of GB.\r\n\r\nA cool feature: Implement an antislashing DB pruning.\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nThis pruning action could be either:\r\n- trigged manually\r\n- automatically\r\n\r\nAfter the pruning, only the few last epochs would remain in the DB (since we normally don't need old epochs).\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\nOf course it is always possible to:\r\n- Stop the validator\r\n- Erase the DB entirely\r\n- Wait for a couple of epochs before restarting the validator to ensure antislashing protection during the transition\r\n- Restart the validator\r\n\r\n\r\n",
